sentence: Home improvement warehouse operator The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) on Tuesday caught a downgrade from analysts at Goldman Sachs, who noted the move was a valuation call.
The firm cut its rating on HD from "Buy" to "Neutral," saying the stock is now approaching fair value.
Goldman maintained its $35 price target, which represents an expected 10.5% upside to the stock's Monday closing price of $31.67.
A Goldman analyst commented that given soft channel checks and tough earnings comparisons in upcoming quarters, "valuation and upside are less compelling."
We had removed shares of HD from our recommended list back on May 25, when the stock was trading at $33.22.
The stock has technical support in the $28-$30 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $34 price level.
We would remain on the sidelines for now.
